OL,3,CCalls for tougher regulation after
OL,4,Conline grooming crimes reach record
OL,5,Clevels
OL,7,FThe government said social media
OL,8,Fcompanies "have a responsibility to
OL,9,Fstop this vile abuse from happening on
OL,10,Ftheir platforms" and that "under the
OL,11,FOnline Safety Act they will have to
OL,12,Fstop this kind of illegal content
OL,13,Fbeing shared."
OL,15,FBut the NSPCC has urged Ofcom to
OL,16,Fstrengthen the bill further, saying
OL,17,Fthere is currently too much focus on
OL,18,Facting after harm has taken place,
OL,19,Frather than being proactive to ensure
OL,20,Fthe design of social media platforms
OL,21,Fdoes not contribute to abuse.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
