OL,3,CCalls for tougher regulation after
OL,4,Conline grooming crimes reach record
OL,5,Clevels
OL,7,F"Under the Online Safety Act they will
OL,8,Fhave to stop this kind of illegal
OL,9,Fcontent being shared on their sites,
OL,10,Fincluding on private and encrypted
OL,11,Fmessaging services, or face
OL,12,Fsignificant fines."
OL,14,FAn Ofcom spokesperson said: "From
OL,15,FDecember, tech firms will be legally
OL,16,Frequired to start taking action under
OL,17,Fthe Online Safety Act, and they'll
OL,18,Fhave to do far more to protect
OL,19,Fchildren.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
